  "title": "PRIOS",
  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial EEG recordings from 6 patients (ages 13-53 years) undergoing clinical evaluation for epilepsy surgery. Cortico-cortical evoked potentials (CCEPs) were recorded via electrocorticography (ECoG) during single-pulse electrical stimulation (SPES) in two conditions: during awake clinical routine and under propofol-induced general anesthesia. The dataset is organized according to BIDS specification and includes electrode localization in MNI305 space derived from individual MRI scans processed with Freesurfer.",
  "methods_description": "Cortico-cortical evoked potentials were recorded using electrocorticography (ECoG) during single-pulse electrical stimulation (SPES) in awake patients (clinical routine) and under propofol anesthesia. Electrode positions were estimated using Freesurfer on individual subject MRI scans and converted to MNI305 space using surface-based non-linear transformation.",
